    • io.sphere.sdk.meta.SphereResources

  • public final class SphereResources

    • Product - Products are the sellable goods in an e-commerce project on SPHERE.IO.
    • ProductProjection - A projected representation of a product shows the product with its current or staged data.
    • Category - Categories are used to organize products in a hierarchical structure.
    • TaxCategory - Tax Categories define how products are to be taxed in different countries.
    • Channel - Channels represent a source or destination of different entities.
    • ProductType - Product types are used to describe common characteristics, most importantly common custom attributes, of many concrete products.
    • ProductDiscount - Product discounts are used to change certain product prices.
    • Cart - A shopping cart holds product variants and can be turned into an order. Each cart either belongs to a registered customer or it is an anonymous cart.
    • Customer - A customer is a person purchasing products. Carts, Orders, Comments and Reviews can be associated to a customer.
    • CustomerGroup - A Customer can be a member of several customer groups (e.g. reseller, gold member). Special prices can be assigned to specific products based on a customer group.
    • Order - An order is the final state of a cart, usually created after a checkout process has been completed.
